        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-07-11 14:21:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nThere is still a slight issue here I do not know how to resolve.\nLets say that we want to capture both stdout and stderror in .sh scripts and log it both in console and the collector.log.\nSo far so good, but we also want to use log4j from java app and use log rotation and truncation that it gives us.\nSo far so good, but once we combine both of these, since java logs into collector.logs and prints to stdout and .sh scripts captures all output, logs in collector.logs are duplicated. ¯\\_(?)_/¯\n\nI think before this can get merged we should solve that, any ideas? :)",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
      {
        "id": "96a912ad440a47a13fa61f298587fc1afa5e633a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3625,
          "name": "Pawel Szalapski",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pawel.szalapski@nokia.com",
          "username": "PawelSzalapski"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-07-11 14:25:06.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nofc taking into account, that we want to have single log file and stdout, no 4 of them as we currently have (collector.log, console.txt, nohup.out, stdout)",
        "patchset_number": 8
      },
